edu.memphis.ccrg.lida.framework.factories

Interface StrategyFactory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Factory, InitializableFactory
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultStrategyFactory

    public interface StrategyFactory
extends InitializableFactory
    The interface for a StrategyFactory. A StrategyFactory supplies objects implementing the Strategy interface. The details of the object creation may be parameterized based on details in an XML configuration file for the factory.

    Classes implementing the StrategyFactory interface must implement the InitializableFactory.

    • Method Detail

      • getStrategy

        <T extends edu.memphis.ccrg.lida.framework.strategies.Strategy> T getStrategy(java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Returns a default implementation matching the specified Strategy interface. If no match is found for the specified interface, or no strategy was registered as the default for that type, then null will be returned.
        Parameters:
        type - a Strategy interface for which an implementation will be returned
        Returns:
        an implementation for the specified interface

      • getStrategy

        <T extends edu.memphis.ccrg.lida.framework.strategies.Strategy> T getStrategy(java.lang.String alias,
                                                                            java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Returns an implementation matching the requested alias and type, or null if the factory does not contain a matching Strategy.
        Parameters:
        alias - an alias for the strategy (set in the XML factory configuration)
        type - the interface corresponding to the desired Strategy implementation
        Returns:
        an object that implements the desired type and is parameterized based on the corresponding alias in the LidaFactories XML configuration.
